{{Infobox academic | honorific_prefix = | name = Catherine E. Renfrew | honorific_suffix = {{post-nominal|GB|MBE}}, {{post-nominal|unlinked=FRCSLT}} | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = 2002 | death_place = | death_cause = | occupation = {{plainlist| * Speech therapist }} | awards = | alma_mater = | thesis_year = | discipline = | sub_discipline = | workplaces = {{plainlist| * United Oxford Hospitals }} }}
'''Catherine Easton Renfrew''',{{post-nominal|GB|MBE}}, {{post-nominal |unlinked=FRCSLT|country=GBR}} (died 2002) was a [[speech therapist]].
==Career== Renfrew was Chief Speech Therapist for [[United Oxford Hospitals]].<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Calnan, J. |author2=Renfrew, C. E. |title=Blowing tests and speech |journal=British Journal of Plastic Surgery |volume=13 |date=1960–1961 |pages=340&ndash;346 |doi=10.1016/S0007-1226(60)80064-1}}</ref>
During her career Renfrew pioneered three forms of expressive language assessments: The ''Renfrew Action Picture Test'' (RAPT), in which a child describes a picture with a single sentence, assesses the length and complexity of spoken sentence structure in 3&ndash;8 year olds; the ''Renfrew Bus Story'' involves story re-telling to assess oral and narrative skills in 3&ndash;8 year olds; and ''Renfrew word finding'' assesses word finding abilities through the naming of pictures and the recording of errors in 3&ndash;9 year olds.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.talkingpoint.org.uk/slts/assessment-children-slcn/expressive-language-assessments |title=Expressive language assessments |publisher=Talking Point |accessdate=13 October 2018}}</ref>
==Awards== Renfrew was elected a Fellow of the [[Royal College of Speech and Language Therapists]] in 1950. She was awarded the Honours of the RCSLT in 1982. Following her death, the RCSLT instituted a biennial award in her memory.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rcslt.org/honours_roll_call_1945-2016 |title=RCSLT Honours Roll Call |publisher=Royal College of Speech and Language Therapists |accessdate=13 October 2018}}</ref> The Catherine Renfrew Memorial Award encourages international collaboration and attendance at non-UK conferences and events through an award of £500.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rcslt.org/members/professional_development/grants_and_awards/catherinerenfrew |title=Catherine Renfrew Memorial Award |publisher=Royal College of Speech and Language Therapists |accessdate=13 October 2018}}</ref>
She was awarded a [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]] in the [[1974 Birthday Honours]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thegazette.co.uk/London/issue/46310/supplement/1 |title=Supplement to the London Gazette, 15th June 1974 |publisher=The Gazette: Official Public Record |accessdate=27 October 2018}}</ref>
==Selected publications== *Renfrew, C. E. and Mitchell, P. 2015 (4th edition). ''Bus story test : a test of narrative speech''. UK, Speechmark Publishing. *Renfrew, C. E. 1997. ''Renfrew language scales / Action picture test''. Bicester, Oxon, Speechmark. *Renfrew, C. E. 1976. "Screening for Language Disorders in Preschool Children", ''Developmental Medicine and Chid Neurology'' 18(1). 97&ndash;98. {{doi|10.1111/j.1469-8749.1976.tb03612.x}} *Renfrew, C. E. 1972. "Prediction of Persisting Speech Defect", ''International Journal of Language and Communication Disorders'' 8(1). 37&ndash;41. {{doi|10.3109/13682827309011583}} *Renfrew, C. E. 1972. ''Speech disorders in children''. Oxford,Pergamon Press. *Renfrew, C. 1968. ''The child who does not talk : report of an International Study Group, St. Mary's College, Durham, 1963 on The Development and the Disorders of Hearing, Language and Speech in Children''. London, Spastics International Medical Publications. *Renfrew, C. E. 1966. "Persistence of the Open Syllable in Defective Articulation", ''Journal of Speech and Hearing Disorders'' 31. 370&ndash;373 {{doi|10.1044/jshd.3104.370}} *Calnan, J. and Renfrew, C. E. 1960&ndash;1961. "Blowing tests and speech", ''[[British Journal of Plastic Surgery]]'' 13. 340&ndash;346. {{doi|10.1016/S0007-1226(60)80064-1}}
