{{Infobox candidate |honorific-prefix = | name = Jean Louis Robinson | honorific-suffix = | image = | alt = | caption = | candidate = [[Malagasy_general_election,_2013#Presidential_elections|President of Madagascar]] | party_election = AVANA | election_date = 20 December 2013 | runningmate = | opponent = [[Hery Rajaonarimampianina]] | incumbent = [[Andry Rajoelina]] |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1952|3|22|df=y}} |birth_place = |birthname = |nationality = [[Madagascar|Malagasy]] |party = AVANA |spouse = |relations = |children = 2 |residence = |alma_mater = |profession = [[Politician]], [[medical doctor]] |religion = |website = {{URL|www.robinson2013.mg}} |footnotes = }}
'''Jean Louis Robinson''' (born 22 March 1952) is a [[Madagascar|Malagasy]] politician. Robinson was the top contender in the first round of the [[Malagasy general election, 2013|2013 general election]] held in September 2013. He lost the run-off against [[Hery Rajaonarimampianina]] in the second round of presidential elections held in December 2013, earning 46.5% of the vote against 53.5% for Rajaonarimampianina. Robinson served in the government of Madagascar as Minister of Health under President [[Marc Ravalomanana]], and he was the Ravalomanana camp's candidate in the 2013 election.<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=19 December 2013 |title=Q&A: Madagascar election run-off |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-25355778 |newspaper= |location= |publisher=BBC News |accessdate=19 December 2013 }}</ref>
